.\" Manpage for Blokator.
.\" Contact tomkoid@proton.me to correct errors or typos.
.TH man 1 "12 Oct 2022" "0.5.0" "blokator man page"
.SH NAME
blokator \- block all ads and spam on your system
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]blokator\f[R] [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple cross-platform and system-wide CLI adblocker
.SH OPTIONS
\f[B]-s, --sync [DOWNLOAD_OPTIONS]\f[R] - sync all added repositories

\f[B]-a, --apply\f[R] - after sync, apply all changes

\f[B]-r, --restore\f[R] - restore backup of hosts file (creates automatically when applying)

\f[B]-b, --backup\f[R] - create a manual backup

\f[B]-m, --add-repo [DOWNLOAD_OPTIONS] [RAW HOSTS FILE TXT URL] \f[R] - add additional repository

\f[B]-d, --del-repo [RAW HOSTS FILE TXT URL]\f[R] - remove additonal repository
.SH DOWNLOAD_OPTIONS
\f[B]-t, --tor\f[R] - use tor when getting data from onion service

\f[B]-A, -tor-all, - use tor for all websites (-t, --tor argument required)
.SH TOR_OPTIONS
\f[B]--tor-bind-address [IP]\f[R] - specify tor proxy ip address (default: 127.0.0.1)

\f[B]--tor-port [PORT]\f[R] - specify tor proxy port (default: 9050)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Tomkoid (tomkoid@proton.me)
